We enter into International Swaps and Derivatives Association (ISDA) master netting agreements within ME&T and Financial
Products that permit the net settlement of amounts owed under their respective derivative contracts. Under these master netting
agreements, net settlement generally permits the company or the counterparty to determine the net amount payable for
contracts due on the same date and in the same currency for similar types of derivative transactions. The master netting
agreements generally also provide for net settlement of all outstanding contracts with a counterparty in the case of an event of
default or a termination event.
Collateral is generally not required of the counterparties or of our company under the master netting agreements. As of
December 31, 2020 and 2019, no cash collateral was received or pledged under the master netting agreements.
