Impaired finance receivables
 
A finance receivable is considered impaired, based on current information and events, if it is probable that Cat Financial will be
unable to collect all amounts due according to the contractual terms.  Impaired finance receivables include finance receivables
that have been restructured and are considered to be troubled debt restructurings.
